places.name: Frigate Bay
places.perex: A popular and lively beach right next to a resort. You won't get bored here - the people-watching and beach activities are endless here.

places.name: Cockleshell Beach
places.perex: A great beach you definitely won't get bored at - plenty of beach activities and friendly locals can be found here. Check out the local pig!

places.name: Brimstone Hill Fortress National Park
places.name_suffix: Saint Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis

places.name_suffix: Saint Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis

places.name: Botanical Gardens of Nevis
places.perex: These gardens are simply outstanding and a must. Features palms, orchids and other tropical plants and also animals.

places.name: Nevis Peak
places.perex: Nevis Peak is a potentially active volcano which is located in the centre of the island of Nevis of the Federation of Saint Kitts and Nevis…

places.name: Reggae Beach
places.name_suffix: Saint Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis

places.name: Cottle Church
places.perex: The Cottle Church was an Anglican Church on the island of Nevis. It was built by Thomas Cottle, a Nevisian lawyer.

places.name: Caribelle Batik
places.perex: The former sugar plantation now houses a batik factory - learn about the process of fabric-dying and get souvenirs from the shop.

places.name: St. Kitts National Museum
places.perex: Learn about the rich history of the islands in the recently restored Treasury building. The diverse collection is worth your attention.

places.name: The Government House
places.perex: Government House, also known as Springfield House, is the official residence of the Governor-General of Saint Kitts and Nevis, current Sir…

places.name: Spooner's Estate
places.perex: Spooner's Estate is a historical cotton and sugar plantation site on Saint Kitts island of Saint Kitts and Nevis, in the Lesser Antilles of…

places.name: St. George's Anglican Church
places.perex: St. George's Anglican Church is an Anglican church in Basseterre, Saint Kitts and Nevis.

places.name: Co-Cathedral of Immaculate Conception
places.perex: The Basseterre Co-Cathedral of Immaculate Conception is a cathedral in the city of Basseterre, St. Kitts and Nevis.

places.name: Wingfield Estate
places.perex: One of the first plantations built on the island. Nowadays, you can see ruins of an aqueduct, a cistern and several buildings here.

places.name: Indepence Square
places.perex: The former slave market is now a gathering place for the locals. The square is filled with palm trees and surrounded by Colonial houses.

places.name: Fairview Great House & Botanical Garden
places.name_suffix: St Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis
places.perex: A beautifully restored 18th-century house. Wonderful interiors, pleasant botanical garden and there is even a pool the guests can use.

places.name: Bath Hotel
places.perex: Bath is a small village on the island of Nevis, in Saint Kitts and Nevis. it is located on the west or Caribbean coast of the island, just…

places.name: Mount Liamuiga
places.perex: Mount Liamuiga is a 3,792-foot stratovolcano which forms the western part of the island of Saint Kitts.

places.name: The Body Haven
places.perex: Relaxing treatments of all sorts might be just what you need - in that case, visit this pleasant spa.

places.name: The Keys Cigar & Rum Bar
places.perex: A cozy, atmospheric bar where you can savour Cuban and Dominican cigars or one of the dozens of rums and other beverages they offer.

places.name: Four Seasons Spa
places.perex: Treat yourself at this luxurious spa. Massages, body treatments and even custom perfume blending is what the spa has to offer.

places.name: Fort Charles
places.perex: Ruins of an old fort that used to protect the British sugar plantations on the island. Nowadays there are only walls and cannons left.

places.name: Emerald Mist Spa
places.perex: A hotel spa offering massages, cosmetic treatments and more. Come here if you'd like to relax and let go of the stress.

places.name: Jewish Cemetery
places.perex: The burial ground used by Brazilian Sephardic Jews is one of the oldest in the Caribbean. An intriguing glimpse into the island's past.

places.name: Spa Nevis
places.perex: A relaxing boutique spa whose beachside location only adds to its atmosphere. Offers the full portfolio of services.

places.name: The Palms Spa
places.perex: A resort-type spa offering massages, facials, body treatments and more. A great way of truly kicking back and letting go of worries.

places.name: Museum of Nevis History
places.perex: Alexander Hamilton was born in this house. Nowadays it has been restored and houses a museum.

places.name: Bloody Point
places.name_suffix: St Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis
places.perex: Bloody Point is a headland in Trinity Palmetto Point Parish, Saint Kitts. The Stone Fort or Bloody River runs towards Bloody Point.

places.name: Friars Bay Beaches
places.perex: Two sandy strips, one on each side of the island. The waves on the north are strong, while the southern waters are calm and good for…

places.name: Lover's Beach
places.perex: A secluded gem of a beach. Perfect for spending time with your loved one in privacy.

places.name: Windsor University School of Medicine
places.name_suffix: Saint Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis
places.perex: Windsor University School of Medicine is a private medical school located in Cayon, Saint Mary Cayon Parish, Saint Kitts and Nevis.

places.name: Dieppe Bay
places.perex: A calm bay with black sandy beaches. The nearby reef helps protect the beach and is a great place for snorkelling.

places.name: Four Seasons Golf Course
places.perex: An 18-hole resort course that features dramatic scenery of the nearby volcano and plenty of challenges like bunkers and water hazards.

places.name: Hermitage Plantation
places.perex: Not just any hotel - this is the oldest house in the Caribbean made completely out of wood. A picturesque sight despite its age.

places.name: Caribe Cafe
places.perex: The first coffeehouse built on the islands. Delicious meals, terrific location and free Wi-Fi are only a few of its perks.

places.name: Mango Orchard Spa
places.perex: A tranquil spa offering all sorts of massages, body treatments, manicure, pedicure and more.

places.name: Black Coral Reef
places.perex: This dive site is home to the rare black coral which is popular in jewellery-making and therefore an endangered species.

places.name: Palms Court Gardens
places.perex: A privately-owned garden with terrific views of the harbour and peaceful atmosphere. There is also a pool where you can spend the day.

places.name: Amazing Grace Experience
places.perex: Discover the history behind the hymn "Amazing Grace" and its author. Your chance to learn about a curious bit of history.

places.name: Fort Charles, St. Kitts
places.perex: Fort Charles, also called Cleverley Point Fort, is a historic British colonial fort site on the island of St.

places.name: Clay Villa Plantation House & Gardens
places.name_suffix: St Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis
places.perex: Over 200 years of history and amazing tropical plants combine on this property. Take the tour given by the owners themselves.

places.name: SkyTrek Safaris
places.perex: Five different zipline tracks that will take you through the sky and over some of the best places on the island.

places.name: Sugar Bay Club
places.name_suffix: Saint Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis

places.name: M.V. Talata Wreck
places.name_suffix: St Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis
places.perex: One of the few wreck dives around the islands. The old freighter has sunk directly on a reef and is home to the local marine life.

places.name: Grid Iron
places.perex: A colourful diving spot. Staghorn corals, all sorts of fish and the occasional shark can be seen here.

places.name: Herbert's Beach
places.perex: This beach is often missed by visitors. Both swimming and snorkelling are popular activities here.

places.name: St. James Windward Church
places.perex: An 18th century church that has been restored several times. The gravestones here are very old and there is also a black crucifix on display.

places.name: Paradise Reef
places.perex: A small wall that has plenty to marvel at if you decide to dive here - marine life, old anchors  and more. A fun dive no matter your skill.

places.name: The Vents
places.perex: The coral reef is rich not just in marine life, but also in geological formations - watch out for the hot water from the gushes!

places.name: La Terrazza
places.name_suffix: Saint Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis

places.name: Friars Bay Reef
places.perex: This reef dive is very easy and beginner-friendly. Plenty of marine life to see here - stingrays, lobsters and angelfish and more.

places.name: Newcastle Beach
places.perex: An extensive beach right by the airport. The currents are strong here, but snorkellers will like this beach.

places.name: Sandy Bank Beach
places.perex: The bay shelters this rural beach, so the waves are calm here. If you want some privacy, this is the beach you should visit.

places.name: Embassy of the Republic of China (Taiwan)
University of Medicine and Health Sciences
places.name_suffix: St Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis

places.name: Coconut Walk Estate
places.perex: A sugar plantation from the 18th century. The tower right next to it still holds itself and is a nice sight.

places.name: Monkey Shoals
places.perex: An extensive coral reef that can be dived at a number of places, although the current is strong here. Also popular for fishing.

places.name: Old Road Bay
places.perex: Site of the first European settlement of the islands. Not much is left, but you can also find Carib petroglyphs here.

places.name: Wreck of River Taw
places.perex: A cargo ship that sunk 30 years ago and is one of the best dive sites in the Caribbean. Corals and schools of fish can be seen here.

places.name: The EL Jones Memorial Golf Course
Banana Bay
places.perex: A spectacular beach that is often missed by visitors. It will be just you, the sea and the resident goats.

places.name: Green Point Reef
places.perex: A rich diving spot. The cavernous reef here is a hangout for many kinds of marine life such as lobsters or corals.

places.name: Half Moon Bay
places.perex: The bay's perfect shape is definitely interesting - watch out for the strong currents here, though. One of the wilder beaches.

places.name: Sandy Point Reef
places.perex: Said to be one of the best reef dives around the islands. The underwater landscape and marine life is really colourful here.

places.name: Christophe Harbour
places.name_suffix: Saint Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis

places.name: Coconut Tree Reef
places.name_suffix: St Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis
places.perex: A colourful reef dive where you can see smaller fish, barracuda or lobsters. Fun and moderately easy dive site.

places.name: Conaree Beach
places.perex: The grey sands here look good, too - just in a different way. A secluded beach with lots of atmosphere that makes up for its lack of…

places.name: Eden Brown Estate
places.perex: The 18th-century plantation is mostly in ruins, but still a popular attraction for the spooky stories that surround it.

places.name: Half Way Tree Village
places.perex: The border between French and British colonies used to run here. Nowadays it's a peaceful village with an intriguing water cistern system.

places.name: White House Bay
places.perex: Not known as a terrific bathing spot, but snorkellers will want to stop by this rocky beach - sea life is vibrant both in the bay and…

places.name: Royal St. Kitts Golf Club
places.name_suffix: Saint Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis

places.name: Cades Bay Beach
places.perex: A large sandy beach that is well-facilitated and always brimming with life. Great for all beach activities and also bird watching.

places.name: Frigate Bay Reef
places.perex: This narrow reef is a fun diving spot no matter your level. Plenty of lobsters, eels and turtles come by here.

places.name: Montpelier House
places.perex: Only a plaque commemorates the house where Horatio Nelson got married. The nearby inn is a nice historical sight, too.

places.name: St. Kitts Marriott Resort & The Royal Beach Casino
places.name_suffix: Saint Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis

places.name: Nisbet Beach
places.perex: Popular especially with the resort guests. Well cared-for and sheltered by the coconut trees, this is one of the beach gems around here.

places.name: Oualie Beach
places.perex: A beautiful sheltered beach right next to a resort. Great for families and anyone who likes to just float in the calm waves.

places.name: Pump Bay
places.name_suffix: Sandy Point, Saint Kitts and Nevis
places.perex: A black, sandy beach popular especially amongst snorkellers. Terrific views of the nearby fortress.

places.name: Sir Thomas Warner Gravestone
places.perex: The final resting place of the first British governor and successful settler of the islands. Look around while you're here.

places.name: Brimstone Shallows
places.name_suffix: St Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis
places.perex: A pristine reef with plenty of marine life around - turtles, barracudas and even the occasional shark. An easy dive.

places.name: Long Haul Bay
places.perex: A beautiful bay with soft waves. Ideal for snorkelling, since the water is calm enough, but kayaking is also popular here.

places.name: St. John's Fig Tree Church
places.perex: A small picturesque church with many old tombstones. Famous for being the place where Nelson's marriage is recorded.

places.name: St. Kitts Sugar Factory and Compound
places.perex: Opened in 1912, this central sugar factory helped St. Kitts sugar industry from a slump.

places.name: Eva Wilkin Gallery
places.perex: The former studio of a great Caribbean artist is now open to everyone - come see artworks from the islands, including her own.

places.name: New River
places.perex: The last sugar mill plantation that closed down in the 50's. Atmospheric ruins that are home to the remains of an enormous steam engine.

places.name: Royal St. Kitts Golf Club
places.name_suffix: Saint Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis

places.name: St. Kitts Eco-Park
places.name_suffix: Saint Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis

places.name: The Marina at Christophe Harbour
places.name_suffix: Saint Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis

places.name: Devil's Cavern
places.perex: A pleasant dive site with plenty  of swim-through caverns where all sorts of fish and other marine life hide.

places.name: Peak Heaven
places.perex: A village that shows life on Nevis in the past. There is also a picnic area, and spa and several monkeys roam around.

places.name: Pinney's Beach
places.perex: The longest beach on Nevis. Has its own rustic charm, but there are also several facilities, so you can easily spend the day here.

places.name: Royal St. Kitts Golf Club
places.perex: One of the best courses in the Caribbean. Well cared-for, with terrific views and 18 challenging holes.

places.name: St. Thomas' Lowland Church
places.perex: The oldest church on the island located near the first European village. Do not miss the memorial to Sir Thomas Warner.

places.name: Nags Head
places.perex: A rock formation that fell into the ocean, creating a wall and a marvellous habitat for all sorts of marine life.

places.name: St Paul's Anglican Church
places.perex: A tiny 19th century church surrounded by a graveyard whose graves are much older than that. A tranquil sight.

places.name: The Finger Reef
places.name_suffix: St Kitts, Saint Kitts and Nevis
places.perex: An exciting divesite - the local colourful reef is home to schools of Creolle wrasse, mackarel and more.

places.name: Turtle Bay
places.perex: A lovely beach with great views of Nevis and facilities to sustain you through the day. An almost untouched gem.

places.name: Wreck of the Corinthian
places.perex: A terrific dive site and a recently sunk wreck that is already bursting with marine life - the fish are very friendly here.
